\frac{\cos\frac{A}{2}}{\sin\frac{A}{2}} = \frac{k(\sin{B} + \sin{C})}{k \sin{A}} = \frac{\sin{B}+\sin{C}}{\sin{A}} = \frac{\cos\frac{A}{2} \cos\frac{B-C}{2}}{\sin\frac{A}{2} \cos\frac{A}{2}}
\frac{\pi}{2} - \Bigl(\frac{B+C}{2}\Bigr)= \pm \frac{B-C}{2}
